Versions after 3 stopped using pymodbus library to avoid future (and current) commands/library breaks.
We use simple python to built the modbus hex query sent to device and simple python to decode the device hex answer.

This one works ok, polling register 10341 = 509TB Battery Voltage = 15.1 at the time of polling.
Note that for polling slave ID had to be zero; though in PLC configuration suite this ID is 1.

python3 python-modbus-poll-7.py --deviceIP 10.242.105.67 --startingregister 10341 --slave 0
[*] Connecting to 10.242.105.67:502
